nts administrative offices and student groups planning high impact and or complex events specialized event planning services may include setting event goals objectives and timelines event design and production budget review venue considerations and logistics registration services ticketing services sustainable green event planning house management and usher staffing liaison planning and or management services with public safety and security risk management office parking and transportation marketing and promotion accessibility resources stanford filming photography webcasting itunes press media and the stanford news service back to top diplomatic protocol services osep provides management and protocol expertise for members of the stanford community in support of high level state national and international visitors and delegations to the stanford campus including visits by heads of state and senior government officials the office also facilitates and manages diplomatic and event protocol arrangements which include planning and managing the dignitary's public speaking logistics and related event arrangements on campus on behalf of the president provost's office or other designated stanford sponsor working with the stanford sponsor or student group on the appropriate approvals invitation and planning processes providing guidance regarding general protocol questions such as flags staging order of precedence seating and gift arrangements diplomatic protocol support and liaison arrangements for dignitary security with the department of public safety management of and liaison planning with risk management office schools departments institutes and the international center regarding meetings with faculty stanford filming photography webcasting itunes press media and the stanford news service accessibility resources parking and transportation the stanford ticket office back to top what we do here are some events produced by osep commencement founders day new student orientati